overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application to ensure it met the acceptance criteria outlined in the Statement
  of Work and a detailed questionnaire specification. The assistant performed an
  initial analysis, identifying several critical gaps and missing features.
  Subsequently, the assistant proceeded to implement these identified items. Key
  implementations included integrating a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness,
  complete with safety warnings in both the web UI and PDF reports. The system
  was enhanced to detect and provide recommendations for Comorbid Insomnia and
  Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome. A new "Resources & Next
  Steps" section was added to the reports, featuring placeholder outbound links
  to relevant medical and educational resources. Furthermore, the Excessive
  Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) scoring was refined to incorporate weighted values
  for specific activities, and the CSV export functionality was significantly
  expanded to include all flattened questionnaire response data. The
  implementation involved modifying TypeScript types, validation schemas, React
  components for the questionnaire and report, and the PDF generation logic.
